### Output
```markdown
Bladder cancer is a leading cause of cancer-related morbidity, yet early 
detection remains challenging due to the invasive nature of cystoscopy and 
limited sensitivity of urine cytology. Here, we present SCOPE2, a 
signal-amplified CRISPR-based platform for rapid, non-invasive detection of 
bladder cancer biomarkers in urine. SCOPE2 integrates isothermal amplification 
with CRISPR-Cas12a trans-cleavage activity, read out via fluorescence 
polarization for enhanced specificity. The platform detects multiple mRNA 
markers within 45 minutes from unprocessed urine samples. In a clinical 
validation study with 156 patient samples, SCOPE2 achieved 92% sensitivity 
and 89% specificity (AUC = 0.94) for bladder cancer detection, outperforming 
conventional urine cytology. SCOPE2 provides a rapid, non-invasive tool for 
bladder cancer screening with potential to improve early detection in 
clinical settings.
```

## Anti-Patterns (AVOID)

| Pattern | Problem | Correction |
|---------|---------|------------|
